WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.944 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:01.944 --> 00:00:10.700 align:middle line:90%


00:00:10.700 --> 00:00:12.210 align:middle line:84%
NARRATOR: The light
on the horizon

00:00:12.210 --> 00:00:19.210 align:middle line:84%
can be a sunrise or a sunset,
a beginning or an end.

00:00:19.210 --> 00:00:22.430 align:middle line:90%


00:00:22.430 --> 00:00:26.690 align:middle line:84%
Some people see the
glass as half empty.

00:00:26.690 --> 00:00:28.942 align:middle line:90%
Others think of it as half full.

00:00:28.942 --> 00:00:38.090 align:middle line:90%


00:00:38.090 --> 00:00:40.065 align:middle line:90%
Perhaps it's neither.

00:00:40.065 --> 00:00:45.811 align:middle line:90%


00:00:45.811 --> 00:00:47.775 align:middle line:90%
[CARS PASSING]

00:00:47.775 --> 00:00:58.577 align:middle line:90%


00:00:58.577 --> 00:01:02.860 align:middle line:84%
No, I never thought I was
going to be a window washer.

00:01:02.860 --> 00:01:05.675 align:middle line:84%
There's no way I'm going to
clean that building, man.

00:01:05.675 --> 00:01:06.390 align:middle line:90%
There's no way.

00:01:06.390 --> 00:01:11.500 align:middle line:90%


00:01:11.500 --> 00:01:14.805 align:middle line:84%
I wanted to have better
education, a better job.

00:01:14.805 --> 00:01:22.420 align:middle line:90%


00:01:22.420 --> 00:01:24.710 align:middle line:84%
I started messing
up in high school,

00:01:24.710 --> 00:01:28.380 align:middle line:84%
just not going to classes,
ditching school, just

00:01:28.380 --> 00:01:29.810 align:middle line:90%
going to band class.

00:01:29.810 --> 00:01:31.876 align:middle line:84%
I just wanted to become
a professional musician.

00:01:31.876 --> 00:01:34.020 align:middle line:84%
I mean, that's why
I'd spend so much

00:01:34.020 --> 00:01:37.390 align:middle line:90%
time in the practice rooms.

00:01:37.390 --> 00:01:41.100 align:middle line:84%
I miss coming in here
and practicing for hours.

00:01:41.100 --> 00:01:43.960 align:middle line:90%


00:01:43.960 --> 00:01:45.984 align:middle line:84%
Look, there's an old
picture of me here.

00:01:45.984 --> 00:01:48.696 align:middle line:90%


00:01:48.696 --> 00:01:50.670 align:middle line:90%
That's me right there.

00:01:50.670 --> 00:01:54.084 align:middle line:84%
And the LE Downtown
Building is back here.

00:01:54.084 --> 00:01:55.250 align:middle line:84%
Who knew I was
going to be cleaning

00:01:55.250 --> 00:01:56.230 align:middle line:90%
all these windows, huh?

00:01:56.230 --> 00:01:59.650 align:middle line:90%


00:01:59.650 --> 00:02:07.340 align:middle line:84%
Um, I think when I first heard
the news that I was going

00:02:07.340 --> 00:02:09.190 align:middle line:90%
to become a father, I tripped.

00:02:09.190 --> 00:02:12.130 align:middle line:90%


00:02:12.130 --> 00:02:15.160 align:middle line:84%
I did want to have kids
but not at an early age.

00:02:15.160 --> 00:02:17.980 align:middle line:84%
I wanted to have
them, maybe, at 35.

00:02:17.980 --> 00:02:21.910 align:middle line:84%
I wanted to have fun in my 20s,
but I have to support my kids.

00:02:21.910 --> 00:02:24.110 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:02:24.110 --> 00:02:26.960 align:middle line:84%
TV SHOW HOST: And now we
return to "Incredible Kids

00:02:26.960 --> 00:02:28.346 align:middle line:90%
and Company."

00:02:28.346 --> 00:02:31.580 align:middle line:90%
[CHEERING]

00:02:31.580 --> 00:02:33.850 align:middle line:84%
Welcome back to "Incredible
Kids and Company."

00:02:33.850 --> 00:02:37.210 align:middle line:84%
We are very pleased to introduce
you to our next special guest.

00:02:37.210 --> 00:02:39.990 align:middle line:84%
This young genius is
a polished magician.

00:02:39.990 --> 00:02:41.740 align:middle line:84%
His name is Todd
Brown, and he's been

00:02:41.740 --> 00:02:44.410 align:middle line:84%
fascinated with the art of magic
since he was eight years old.

00:02:44.410 --> 00:02:48.670 align:middle line:84%
We are proud to present Todd
Brown, magician extraordinaire.

00:02:48.670 --> 00:02:50.658 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:02:50.658 --> 00:03:05.568 align:middle line:90%


00:03:05.568 --> 00:03:07.556 align:middle line:90%
[APPLAUSE]

00:03:07.556 --> 00:03:10.050 align:middle line:90%


00:03:10.050 --> 00:03:12.600 align:middle line:90%
I haven't aged a day, have I?

00:03:12.600 --> 00:03:15.160 align:middle line:84%
My stage name-- I don't know
if I admitted this yet or not

00:03:15.160 --> 00:03:17.660 align:middle line:84%
in this documentary, but
my stage name at the time

00:03:17.660 --> 00:03:19.280 align:middle line:90%
was Flasho the Magician.

00:03:19.280 --> 00:03:21.510 align:middle line:90%
Did we ever discuss that?

00:03:21.510 --> 00:03:23.375 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, maybe that
shouldn't make it in.

00:03:23.375 --> 00:03:30.830 align:middle line:84%
I have my performance
case-- you know, top hat.

00:03:30.830 --> 00:03:32.560 align:middle line:90%
Got to have one of those.

00:03:32.560 --> 00:03:36.690 align:middle line:84%
This is the one I produced
my bunny rabbit out of.

00:03:36.690 --> 00:03:39.450 align:middle line:84%
His name-- it to be Fluffy,
but now it's Pancake.

00:03:39.450 --> 00:03:44.280 align:middle line:90%
Um, do bands of steel that--

00:03:44.280 --> 00:03:45.336 align:middle line:90%
INTERVIEWER: What?

00:03:45.336 --> 00:03:50.101 align:middle line:84%
Kind of go together like that,
come apart, stuff like that.

00:03:50.101 --> 00:03:50.800 align:middle line:90%
INTERVIEWER: Typical.

00:03:50.800 --> 00:03:52.600 align:middle line:84%
TODD (VOICEOVER): And I
absolutely thought about being

00:03:52.600 --> 00:03:53.950 align:middle line:90%
a magician full time.

00:03:53.950 --> 00:03:55.050 align:middle line:90%
That would've been great.

00:03:55.050 --> 00:03:58.330 align:middle line:84%
I had this appearance on
a TV show when I was 16.

00:03:58.330 --> 00:04:01.863 align:middle line:84%
And I was always at my
school talent shows.

00:04:01.863 --> 00:04:06.600 align:middle line:84%
And I just thought
I was on a roll.

00:04:06.600 --> 00:04:09.380 align:middle line:84%
And then, when I computed
on a national level

00:04:09.380 --> 00:04:11.010 align:middle line:84%
at one of the
national conventions,

00:04:11.010 --> 00:04:13.105 align:middle line:84%
I would say I lost
to a very famous

00:04:13.105 --> 00:04:14.510 align:middle line:84%
magician named
Lance Burton who had

00:04:14.510 --> 00:04:16.930 align:middle line:90%
a Vegas show for many years.

00:04:16.930 --> 00:04:19.709 align:middle line:84%
And I realized, at
that point, it was

00:04:19.709 --> 00:04:21.914 align:middle line:90%
time to find another career.

00:04:21.914 --> 00:04:24.570 align:middle line:84%
I don't know how we
got into this position.

00:04:24.570 --> 00:04:26.830 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:04:26.830 --> 00:04:29.330 align:middle line:84%
I didn't say I going to move
my shoulder over, move my body.

00:04:29.330 --> 00:04:32.270 align:middle line:84%
No, the music pushed
my over, which is why I

00:04:32.270 --> 00:04:35.060 align:middle line:90%
call it "One Buttock Playing."

00:04:35.060 --> 00:04:37.190 align:middle line:84%
Now, I had an
amazing experience.

00:04:37.190 --> 00:04:38.560 align:middle line:90%
I was 45 years old.

00:04:38.560 --> 00:04:40.470 align:middle line:84%
I've been conducting
for 20 years.

00:04:40.470 --> 00:04:43.410 align:middle line:84%
And I, suddenly,
had a realization.

00:04:43.410 --> 00:04:47.120 align:middle line:84%
The conductor of an orchestra
doesn't make a sound.

00:04:47.120 --> 00:04:49.570 align:middle line:84%
My picture appears on
the front of the CD.

00:04:49.570 --> 00:04:51.570 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:04:51.570 --> 00:04:53.570 align:middle line:90%


00:04:53.570 --> 00:04:55.660 align:middle line:84%
And that changed
everything for me.

00:04:55.660 --> 00:04:57.550 align:middle line:90%
It was totally life changing.

00:04:57.550 --> 00:05:00.450 align:middle line:84%
People in my orchestra came up
and said, Ben, what happened?

00:05:00.450 --> 00:05:01.290 align:middle line:90%
That's what happened.

00:05:01.290 --> 00:05:07.074 align:middle line:84%
I realized my job was to awaken
possibility in other people.

00:05:07.074 --> 00:05:10.448 align:middle line:90%
[BEN SINGING CLASSICAL MUSIC]

00:05:10.448 --> 00:05:17.690 align:middle line:90%


00:05:17.690 --> 00:05:20.570 align:middle line:84%
BEN: That was a tremendous
transformational moment

00:05:20.570 --> 00:05:22.490 align:middle line:90%
because it changed everything.

00:05:22.490 --> 00:05:26.670 align:middle line:84%
I was very emotionally
up and down.

00:05:26.670 --> 00:05:29.120 align:middle line:90%
[MAKING NOSIES]

00:05:29.120 --> 00:05:32.176 align:middle line:84%
So, if things were going
well, I'd be very excited.

00:05:32.176 --> 00:05:36.620 align:middle line:84%
[SCREAMS] If things were going
bad, I'd be very depressed.

00:05:36.620 --> 00:05:39.130 align:middle line:84%
[IMITATING INSTRUMENTS]
My thought was,

00:05:39.130 --> 00:05:40.460 align:middle line:90%
they're just following me.

00:05:40.460 --> 00:05:44.580 align:middle line:84%
And I'm going to push them
around until they obey my will.

00:05:44.580 --> 00:05:47.425 align:middle line:90%
[IMITATING INSTRUMENTS]

00:05:47.425 --> 00:05:50.151 align:middle line:84%
It changed immediately my
relationship to the players.

00:05:50.151 --> 00:05:52.857 align:middle line:90%


00:05:52.857 --> 00:05:54.210 align:middle line:90%
I'm so glad you came.

00:05:54.210 --> 00:05:57.580 align:middle line:84%
As I suddenly became interested
in knowing whether I was,

00:05:57.580 --> 00:06:00.900 align:middle line:84%
in fact, enabling
them to realize

00:06:00.900 --> 00:06:02.871 align:middle line:90%
the possibility that they are.

00:06:02.871 --> 00:06:04.715 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:06:04.715 --> 00:06:07.020 align:middle line:90%


00:06:07.020 --> 00:06:09.540 align:middle line:84%
Because if something
happens to you

00:06:09.540 --> 00:06:11.980 align:middle line:84%
and it's not a particularly
cheerful thing--

00:06:11.980 --> 00:06:15.540 align:middle line:84%
like a divorce, for
instance, or the loss

00:06:15.540 --> 00:06:19.740 align:middle line:84%
of a wonderful person or
illness or whatever it may be--

00:06:19.740 --> 00:06:22.160 align:middle line:90%
it's very hard.

00:06:22.160 --> 00:06:24.100 align:middle line:90%
[CRICKETS]

00:06:24.100 --> 00:06:27.980 align:middle line:90%


00:06:27.980 --> 00:06:30.720 align:middle line:84%
JORGE (VOICEOVER): The hardest
part is waking up at 4:00

00:06:30.720 --> 00:06:34.430 align:middle line:84%
AM or 3:00 AM--
whatever the time you're

00:06:34.430 --> 00:06:36.977 align:middle line:90%
supposed to be at the building.

00:06:36.977 --> 00:06:38.973 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:06:38.973 --> 00:07:12.910 align:middle line:90%


00:07:12.910 --> 00:07:15.490 align:middle line:84%
I mean, once you have kids,
it's just life changing.

00:07:15.490 --> 00:07:17.470 align:middle line:84%
You can do stuff
that you want to do,

00:07:17.470 --> 00:07:19.125 align:middle line:84%
but it's just
going to be harder.

00:07:19.125 --> 00:07:21.105 align:middle line:90%
[HELICOPTER]

00:07:21.105 --> 00:07:24.075 align:middle line:90%


00:07:24.075 --> 00:07:26.055 align:middle line:90%
[SPEAKING SPANISH]

00:07:26.055 --> 00:07:32.990 align:middle line:90%


00:07:32.990 --> 00:07:35.145 align:middle line:84%
You just have to be
very alert, to think,

00:07:35.145 --> 00:07:40.440 align:middle line:84%
you know, one false step and
you fall off the building

00:07:40.440 --> 00:07:44.020 align:middle line:90%
and things go bad for everyone.

00:07:44.020 --> 00:07:47.470 align:middle line:90%


00:07:47.470 --> 00:07:49.100 align:middle line:90%
I mean, I can't say no.

00:07:49.100 --> 00:07:52.703 align:middle line:84%
It's just a
necessity to go work.

00:07:52.703 --> 00:07:54.667 align:middle line:90%
[SPEAKING SPANISH]

00:07:54.667 --> 00:08:02.530 align:middle line:90%


00:08:02.530 --> 00:08:06.402 align:middle line:84%
It's just difficult to get to
wherever you want to get to.

00:08:06.402 --> 00:08:08.705 align:middle line:84%
So, this is not
about you anymore.

00:08:08.705 --> 00:08:12.274 align:middle line:84%
This is about you, your
wife, and your kid. [LAUGHS]

00:08:12.274 --> 00:08:14.238 align:middle line:90%
[SPEAKING SPANISH]

00:08:14.238 --> 00:08:16.202 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:08:16.202 --> 00:08:26.022 align:middle line:90%


00:08:26.022 --> 00:08:28.800 align:middle line:84%
To this day, I can't
even go to the local park

00:08:28.800 --> 00:08:30.720 align:middle line:90%
because it's all dangerous.

00:08:30.720 --> 00:08:33.280 align:middle line:84%
I don't have enough
money to support

00:08:33.280 --> 00:08:35.970 align:middle line:90%
my family in a safer place.

00:08:35.970 --> 00:08:38.571 align:middle line:84%
That's why I'm working
so hard these days,

00:08:38.571 --> 00:08:39.804 align:middle line:84%
to get them out of
this neighborhood.

00:08:39.804 --> 00:08:44.980 align:middle line:90%


00:08:44.980 --> 00:08:46.510 align:middle line:90%
So I'm going through a divorce.

00:08:46.510 --> 00:08:48.320 align:middle line:90%
I wonder what's next.

00:08:48.320 --> 00:08:52.660 align:middle line:84%
That's very hard to do because,
in the moment of the loss

00:08:52.660 --> 00:08:55.440 align:middle line:84%
of an important relationship--
or something where you think

00:08:55.440 --> 00:08:57.510 align:middle line:84%
your whole world
is created around,

00:08:57.510 --> 00:09:00.930 align:middle line:84%
that idea of being
married, for instance--

00:09:00.930 --> 00:09:03.626 align:middle line:84%
the assumption is that
it's going to be terrible.

00:09:03.626 --> 00:09:05.870 align:middle line:90%
Not at all.

00:09:05.870 --> 00:09:09.250 align:middle line:84%
Mainly, I will say,
Rose had the discipline

00:09:09.250 --> 00:09:12.970 align:middle line:84%
to constantly come up with
this idea that, no, no, no.

00:09:12.970 --> 00:09:14.560 align:middle line:90%
This isn't the end.

00:09:14.560 --> 00:09:16.040 align:middle line:90%
It's just a different form.

00:09:16.040 --> 00:09:19.290 align:middle line:84%
I didn't see it at first
because I was [GRUMBLES]

00:09:19.290 --> 00:09:20.185 align:middle line:90%
trying to get it back.

00:09:20.185 --> 00:09:22.380 align:middle line:84%
Well, I'm the
philosopher in the group.

00:09:22.380 --> 00:09:25.430 align:middle line:90%
And so--

00:09:25.430 --> 00:09:27.790 align:middle line:84%
BEN: Because what normally
happens when two people

00:09:27.790 --> 00:09:30.710 align:middle line:84%
separate or divorce is they
try and make the other person

00:09:30.710 --> 00:09:33.640 align:middle line:84%
as wrong as possible,
get all the evidence they

00:09:33.640 --> 00:09:35.320 align:middle line:90%
can about how wrong they were.

00:09:35.320 --> 00:09:37.170 align:middle line:84%
And then they get
lawyers to come in there

00:09:37.170 --> 00:09:39.640 align:middle line:84%
and bash the other
as much in order

00:09:39.640 --> 00:09:42.020 align:middle line:90%
to justify what went wrong.

00:09:42.020 --> 00:09:45.130 align:middle line:84%
And what Rose did was the
exact opposite, which was,

00:09:45.130 --> 00:09:46.270 align:middle line:90%
this is not working.

00:09:46.270 --> 00:09:49.480 align:middle line:84%
This form of our
relationship is not working.

00:09:49.480 --> 00:09:52.880 align:middle line:90%
So Let's create a new form.

00:09:52.880 --> 00:09:55.650 align:middle line:90%
That's possibility.

00:09:55.650 --> 00:09:58.260 align:middle line:84%
TODD: As disappointed as
I was, to some degree,

00:09:58.260 --> 00:10:00.860 align:middle line:84%
knowing I was not going
to win this competition,

00:10:00.860 --> 00:10:03.810 align:middle line:90%
I was OK with that.

00:10:03.810 --> 00:10:08.260 align:middle line:84%
Magic has been such
an important component

00:10:08.260 --> 00:10:11.565 align:middle line:84%
of my life in ways I never could
have expected or anticipated.

00:10:11.565 --> 00:10:15.535 align:middle line:90%


00:10:15.535 --> 00:10:16.234 align:middle line:90%
Cool.

00:10:16.234 --> 00:10:20.518 align:middle line:90%


00:10:20.518 --> 00:10:22.021 align:middle line:84%
But yeah, I get a lot
of thank-you letters

00:10:22.021 --> 00:10:23.960 align:middle line:84%
for performing.
They're really nice.

00:10:23.960 --> 00:10:26.240 align:middle line:84%
"Todd, my young children
and I thoroughly

00:10:26.240 --> 00:10:28.020 align:middle line:84%
enjoyed your very
professional performance

00:10:28.020 --> 00:10:29.980 align:middle line:90%
in last night's variety show.

00:10:29.980 --> 00:10:33.070 align:middle line:84%
My youngest song, age
seven, was fascinated.

00:10:33.070 --> 00:10:36.160 align:middle line:84%
I think he may be making
career plans of his own.

00:10:36.160 --> 00:10:38.180 align:middle line:84%
Thanks again, and good
luck in tonight's show.

00:10:38.180 --> 00:10:40.120 align:middle line:90%
Mrs. Barber."

00:10:40.120 --> 00:10:42.730 align:middle line:84%
I still love it and it's
fun to fund a reminisce.

00:10:42.730 --> 00:10:50.730 align:middle line:84%
But that was then this is now,
so it's all-- yeah, it's fine.

00:10:50.730 --> 00:10:54.660 align:middle line:90%


00:10:54.660 --> 00:10:57.250 align:middle line:90%
I've never really had a job.

00:10:57.250 --> 00:10:59.620 align:middle line:84%
I've always kind of
done my own thing.

00:10:59.620 --> 00:11:02.180 align:middle line:84%
I've always been
an entrepreneur.

00:11:02.180 --> 00:11:04.300 align:middle line:84%
But there have been a
few opportunities for me

00:11:04.300 --> 00:11:06.470 align:middle line:90%
to give back using magic.

00:11:06.470 --> 00:11:08.525 align:middle line:84%
And one of those has been
performing at hospitals.

00:11:08.525 --> 00:11:14.762 align:middle line:90%


00:11:14.762 --> 00:11:18.260 align:middle line:84%
You know, a lot times things
that don't go your way lead

00:11:18.260 --> 00:11:20.380 align:middle line:90%
you to something else better.

00:11:20.380 --> 00:11:24.190 align:middle line:90%


00:11:24.190 --> 00:11:28.030 align:middle line:84%
I got interested in magic at
a pretty young age as a hobby.

00:11:28.030 --> 00:11:32.190 align:middle line:84%
And now, to think that I can,
maybe, inspire other kids-- I

00:11:32.190 --> 00:11:33.720 align:middle line:90%
love when those moments happen.

00:11:33.720 --> 00:11:37.716 align:middle line:90%


00:11:37.716 --> 00:11:40.060 align:middle line:84%
Hopefully I can make this
kid's day a little better.

00:11:40.060 --> 00:11:42.794 align:middle line:84%
It sounds like he's had
a pretty rough morning.

00:11:42.794 --> 00:11:44.706 align:middle line:90%
[MACHINES BEEPING]

00:11:44.706 --> 00:11:48.530 align:middle line:90%


00:11:48.530 --> 00:11:50.442 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:11:50.442 --> 00:11:52.370 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:11:52.370 --> 00:11:53.560 align:middle line:90%
It's an amazing world.

00:11:53.560 --> 00:11:58.680 align:middle line:84%
I mean, it's just--
it's a world of such joy

00:11:58.680 --> 00:12:01.740 align:middle line:84%
and open heartedness
and excitement.

00:12:01.740 --> 00:12:03.520 align:middle line:84%
And all these kids in
the youth orchestra,

00:12:03.520 --> 00:12:07.510 align:middle line:84%
particularly-- they're the ones
who are getting it full blast.

00:12:07.510 --> 00:12:09.195 align:middle line:84%
And you can see
it in their faces.

00:12:09.195 --> 00:12:12.600 align:middle line:84%
You can see it in their
joy and excitement,

00:12:12.600 --> 00:12:14.566 align:middle line:90%
It's an amazing thing.

00:12:14.566 --> 00:12:16.430 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:12:16.430 --> 00:12:22.770 align:middle line:90%


00:12:22.770 --> 00:12:26.830 align:middle line:84%
My father, he had a
huge influence on me.

00:12:26.830 --> 00:12:30.900 align:middle line:84%
In fact, I met one of my
students in the corridor

00:12:30.900 --> 00:12:32.730 align:middle line:90%
after he died.

00:12:32.730 --> 00:12:35.050 align:middle line:84%
I said, my father
died yesterday.

00:12:35.050 --> 00:12:36.835 align:middle line:90%
And she started crying.

00:12:36.835 --> 00:12:38.780 align:middle line:84%
And I said, but you
didn't know my father.

00:12:38.780 --> 00:12:39.970 align:middle line:90%
She said, yes, I did.

00:12:39.970 --> 00:12:41.658 align:middle line:90%
I knew him through you.

00:12:41.658 --> 00:12:43.650 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:12:43.650 --> 00:12:54.120 align:middle line:90%


00:12:54.120 --> 00:12:58.690 align:middle line:84%
My father, at age 95-- when he
was lying on his deathbed-- was

00:12:58.690 --> 00:13:01.750 align:middle line:84%
to say, as the
last thing he said,

00:13:01.750 --> 00:13:05.700 align:middle line:84%
is there anything
I can do to help?

00:13:05.700 --> 00:13:08.850 align:middle line:90%
That to me is a discipline.

00:13:08.850 --> 00:13:12.170 align:middle line:84%
That's a long life
in which he realized

00:13:12.170 --> 00:13:14.930 align:middle line:90%
he suffered extraordinarily.

00:13:14.930 --> 00:13:17.030 align:middle line:84%
But in the end, he
understood the most

00:13:17.030 --> 00:13:19.505 align:middle line:84%
important thing was to do
something for other people.

00:13:19.505 --> 00:13:27.920 align:middle line:90%


00:13:27.920 --> 00:13:29.405 align:middle line:90%
Hi, there.

00:13:29.405 --> 00:13:31.400 align:middle line:90%
I hear your name's Blake.

00:13:31.400 --> 00:13:32.553 align:middle line:90%
My name's Todd.

00:13:32.553 --> 00:13:34.462 align:middle line:84%
Nice to meet you, Blake.
-Hi.

00:13:34.462 --> 00:13:35.987 align:middle line:84%
-How's everything going?
-Good.

00:13:35.987 --> 00:13:38.658 align:middle line:84%
Doing all right?
Do you know why I'm here?

00:13:38.658 --> 00:13:40.040 align:middle line:90%
You're a magician.

00:13:40.040 --> 00:13:40.820 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:13:40.820 --> 00:13:42.590 align:middle line:84%
Have you ever seen
a magician before?

00:13:42.590 --> 00:13:43.670 align:middle line:90%
What about a magical rainbow?

00:13:43.670 --> 00:13:45.231 align:middle line:84%
Have you ever seen
one of those, Blake?

00:13:45.231 --> 00:13:45.930 align:middle line:90%
Watch carefully.

00:13:45.930 --> 00:13:46.840 align:middle line:84%
We're going to make
one, all right?

00:13:46.840 --> 00:13:48.080 align:middle line:84%
Ready, right here.
See it?

00:13:48.080 --> 00:13:48.900 align:middle line:90%
Right there.

00:13:48.900 --> 00:13:50.060 align:middle line:90%
See it?

00:13:50.060 --> 00:13:51.660 align:middle line:84%
No, it's invisible.
That's why you couldn't see it.

00:13:51.660 --> 00:13:52.360 align:middle line:90%
Ready, though?

00:13:52.360 --> 00:13:53.846 align:middle line:90%
Watch.

00:13:53.846 --> 00:13:57.350 align:middle line:84%
Does that make you go,
ooh, ahh, maybe a little?

00:13:57.350 --> 00:13:58.820 align:middle line:84%
What do you think?
-Yeah.

00:13:58.820 --> 00:14:00.180 align:middle line:90%
Is that pretty cool?

00:14:00.180 --> 00:14:02.090 align:middle line:84%
Maybe when I'm done I can
teach you some tricks.

00:14:02.090 --> 00:14:02.865 align:middle line:90%
Would you like that?

00:14:02.865 --> 00:14:05.042 align:middle line:90%
All right, cool.

00:14:05.042 --> 00:14:07.585 align:middle line:84%
It helps you get
the girls, you know.

00:14:07.585 --> 00:14:10.360 align:middle line:84%
It didn't help me,
but apparently it

00:14:10.360 --> 00:14:11.590 align:middle line:90%
can help other magicians.

00:14:11.590 --> 00:14:13.510 align:middle line:84%
Can you take one of
those crayons out?

00:14:13.510 --> 00:14:14.290 align:middle line:90%
Don't show me, though.

00:14:14.290 --> 00:14:15.710 align:middle line:90%
I don't want to know, OK?

00:14:15.710 --> 00:14:18.710 align:middle line:84%
And can you put it in my
hand so I can't see it?

00:14:18.710 --> 00:14:20.600 align:middle line:84%
All right, I'm going
to turn around.

00:14:20.600 --> 00:14:23.105 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to try to
read your mind, OK?

00:14:23.105 --> 00:14:24.600 align:middle line:90%
All right, Blake, let's see.

00:14:24.600 --> 00:14:26.460 align:middle line:90%
Concentrate, concentrate.

00:14:26.460 --> 00:14:30.360 align:middle line:84%
I'm not sure what color, but
I'm feeling, like, the ocean

00:14:30.360 --> 00:14:33.620 align:middle line:90%
or some ocean or the sky ocean.

00:14:33.620 --> 00:14:36.940 align:middle line:84%
Why am I thinking
of-- was it blue?

00:14:36.940 --> 00:14:38.400 align:middle line:90%
Hey it was blue!

00:14:38.400 --> 00:14:39.230 align:middle line:90%
Good job.

00:14:39.230 --> 00:14:42.050 align:middle line:90%
You sent me some good messages.

00:14:42.050 --> 00:14:43.265 align:middle line:84%
Do you want to
know how I did it?

00:14:43.265 --> 00:14:44.340 align:middle line:90%
Do you know?

00:14:44.340 --> 00:14:45.436 align:middle line:90%
Do you any ideas?

00:14:45.436 --> 00:14:47.600 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, what's on my thumbnail?

00:14:47.600 --> 00:14:49.850 align:middle line:90%
Oh.

00:14:49.850 --> 00:14:56.150 align:middle line:84%
When I turned this way, I drew
on my thumb with the crayon.

00:14:56.150 --> 00:14:57.785 align:middle line:84%
So when I turned back
this way and pretended

00:14:57.785 --> 00:15:00.245 align:middle line:84%
to read your mind, guess
what I'm looking at?

00:15:00.245 --> 00:15:01.190 align:middle line:90%
The color.

00:15:01.190 --> 00:15:02.650 align:middle line:90%
A blue thumbnail.

00:15:02.650 --> 00:15:05.260 align:middle line:84%
I started doing magic when
I was about eight years old.

00:15:05.260 --> 00:15:07.660 align:middle line:84%
Magic was something that I
enjoyed doing as a hobby.

00:15:07.660 --> 00:15:09.790 align:middle line:90%
And I was in competitions.

00:15:09.790 --> 00:15:12.620 align:middle line:84%
And, you know, it's just a good
way to keep your mind going

00:15:12.620 --> 00:15:13.620 align:middle line:90%
and give you something to do.

00:15:13.620 --> 00:15:17.220 align:middle line:84%
So maybe that's something you
can work on one of these days.

00:15:17.220 --> 00:15:21.121 align:middle line:84%
Would you like to keep the
crayons and work on that?

00:15:21.121 --> 00:15:21.820 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:15:21.820 --> 00:15:27.310 align:middle line:84%
Every time I've done a
volunteer gig using magic,

00:15:27.310 --> 00:15:29.000 align:middle line:90%
it's very gratifying.

00:15:29.000 --> 00:15:31.430 align:middle line:84%
I don't know how many
talents I have in this world,

00:15:31.430 --> 00:15:34.940 align:middle line:84%
but this is one I have and
something I'm able to do

00:15:34.940 --> 00:15:36.250 align:middle line:90%
to bring some joy to people.

00:15:36.250 --> 00:15:42.730 align:middle line:90%


00:15:42.730 --> 00:15:44.930 align:middle line:84%
JORGE (VOICEOVER): I mean,
now I know that I cannot

00:15:44.930 --> 00:15:46.530 align:middle line:90%
become a professional musician.

00:15:46.530 --> 00:15:49.750 align:middle line:84%
But I play music
almost every weekend.

00:15:49.750 --> 00:15:52.440 align:middle line:90%
And I get paid doing it.

00:15:52.440 --> 00:15:54.956 align:middle line:84%
That helps my
dream a little bit.

00:15:54.956 --> 00:15:56.948 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:15:56.948 --> 00:16:10.730 align:middle line:90%


00:16:10.730 --> 00:16:13.390 align:middle line:84%
I usually just use
that money for Sundays

00:16:13.390 --> 00:16:15.015 align:middle line:90%
and spend time with my kids.

00:16:15.015 --> 00:16:21.810 align:middle line:90%


00:16:21.810 --> 00:16:24.350 align:middle line:84%
Every morning, they start
poking me in my bed.

00:16:24.350 --> 00:16:26.280 align:middle line:84%
So, I mean, I'd never
had that before.

00:16:26.280 --> 00:16:28.490 align:middle line:84%
And it's just a
warm feeling inside.

00:16:28.490 --> 00:16:31.420 align:middle line:84%
I mean, they wake
me up and, hey, Dad,

00:16:31.420 --> 00:16:32.460 align:middle line:90%
it's time for breakfast.

00:16:32.460 --> 00:16:33.860 align:middle line:90%
Or, hey, Dad let's go to sleep.

00:16:33.860 --> 00:16:34.815 align:middle line:90%
Or let's watch a movie.

00:16:34.815 --> 00:16:40.280 align:middle line:90%


00:16:40.280 --> 00:16:45.131 align:middle line:84%
Without them, I don't think I'd
be able to keep it together.

00:16:45.131 --> 00:16:47.586 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:16:47.586 --> 00:17:05.760 align:middle line:90%


00:17:05.760 --> 00:17:07.287 align:middle line:90%
A.

00:17:07.287 --> 00:17:09.223 align:middle line:90%
[A NOTE ON VIOLIN]

00:17:09.223 --> 00:17:11.159 align:middle line:90%
[INSTRUMENTS TUNING]

00:17:11.159 --> 00:17:19.400 align:middle line:90%


00:17:19.400 --> 00:17:24.000 align:middle line:84%
Shostakovish, starting
at the allegro.

00:17:24.000 --> 00:17:25.339 align:middle line:84%
I'll give you two
bars for nothing.

00:17:25.339 --> 00:17:27.569 align:middle line:90%
1, 1, 2, 1, 2.

00:17:27.569 --> 00:17:29.649 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:17:29.649 --> 00:17:37.520 align:middle line:84%
Can we do the very first
[IMITATING MUSIC] like that?

00:17:37.520 --> 00:17:39.169 align:middle line:90%
1, 2, 1.

00:17:39.169 --> 00:17:41.165 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:17:41.165 --> 00:18:02.351 align:middle line:90%


00:18:02.351 --> 00:18:03.050 align:middle line:90%
Shhh.

00:18:03.050 --> 00:18:08.160 align:middle line:90%


00:18:08.160 --> 00:18:12.150 align:middle line:84%
Whatever happens, whatever
the circumstances,

00:18:12.150 --> 00:18:13.970 align:middle line:90%
live into that possibility.

00:18:13.970 --> 00:18:16.100 align:middle line:84%
When you're alive
to possibility,

00:18:16.100 --> 00:18:18.380 align:middle line:90%
you're awake, aware.

00:18:18.380 --> 00:18:20.455 align:middle line:84%
We can wake up in the
morning and, [GRUMBLES]

00:18:20.455 --> 00:18:22.590 align:middle line:90%
it's going to be a horrible day.

00:18:22.590 --> 00:18:24.574 align:middle line:84%
Or we can wake up in
the morning and say,

00:18:24.574 --> 00:18:25.840 align:middle line:84%
I wonder what's going
to happen today.

00:18:25.840 --> 00:18:27.464 align:middle line:90%
I can't wait.

00:18:27.464 --> 00:18:32.050 align:middle line:84%
That's a wonderful state
of mind, state of being.

00:18:32.050 --> 00:18:36.060 align:middle line:84%
Everything that happens
is an opportunity.

00:18:36.060 --> 00:18:40.640 align:middle line:90%
What we make of it is up to us.

00:18:40.640 --> 00:18:43.160 align:middle line:84%
If I had pursued magic
full time early on,

00:18:43.160 --> 00:18:45.790 align:middle line:84%
maybe I wouldn't have
my wonderful family.

00:18:45.790 --> 00:18:47.890 align:middle line:84%
Maybe I'd have a
whole different life.

00:18:47.890 --> 00:18:52.220 align:middle line:84%
I'd be living on cruise
ships and in hotels and have

00:18:52.220 --> 00:18:55.156 align:middle line:90%
a drinking problem. [LAUGHS]

00:18:55.156 --> 00:18:57.112 align:middle line:90%
[BABY LAUGHING]

00:18:57.112 --> 00:18:59.714 align:middle line:90%


00:18:59.714 --> 00:19:01.080 align:middle line:84%
JORGE: If you fall
down, you have to know

00:19:01.080 --> 00:19:03.900 align:middle line:90%
how to get up, when to get up.

00:19:03.900 --> 00:19:05.255 align:middle line:90%
I almost tripped.

00:19:05.255 --> 00:19:07.750 align:middle line:90%
But then I got up again.

00:19:07.750 --> 00:19:09.680 align:middle line:90%
And then I said to myself, OK.

00:19:09.680 --> 00:19:11.020 align:middle line:90%
I'm going to become a father.

00:19:11.020 --> 00:19:13.340 align:middle line:90%
[CLAPPING A BEAT]

00:19:13.340 --> 00:19:17.470 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS] We'll see, right?

00:19:17.470 --> 00:19:18.720 align:middle line:84%
And everybody's
got shining eyes.

00:19:18.720 --> 00:19:21.090 align:middle line:84%
The main thing to realize
is that possibility

00:19:21.090 --> 00:19:22.440 align:middle line:90%
shows up in the eyes.

00:19:22.440 --> 00:19:24.180 align:middle line:90%
Look at their eyes, in the eyes.

00:19:24.180 --> 00:19:25.565 align:middle line:84%
To some degree, you
go with the flow.

00:19:25.565 --> 00:19:30.150 align:middle line:84%
And you go with, kind of, where
the universe is taking you.

00:19:30.150 --> 00:19:32.215 align:middle line:90%
I'm still 23 years old.

00:19:32.215 --> 00:19:35.090 align:middle line:90%
I think I've learned a lot.

00:19:35.090 --> 00:19:38.102 align:middle line:84%
I think there's still
much more for me to learn.

00:19:38.102 --> 00:19:40.740 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS] Life is great.

00:19:40.740 --> 00:19:42.550 align:middle line:90%
I mean, it really is amazing.

00:19:42.550 --> 00:19:45.130 align:middle line:84%
I'm incredibly
lucky to be alive.

00:19:45.130 --> 00:19:48.020 align:middle line:84%
I mean, isn't it an
extraordinary privilege

00:19:48.020 --> 00:19:50.400 align:middle line:90%
to be alive?

00:19:50.400 --> 00:19:52.400 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:19:52.400 --> 00:20:53.170 align:middle line:90%


00:20:53.170 --> 00:20:53.870 align:middle line:90%
I'm 51.

00:20:53.870 --> 00:20:55.728 align:middle line:90%
I still like to feel cool.

00:20:55.728 --> 00:20:59.220 align:middle line:10%
My ring makes mine.

00:20:59.220 --> 00:21:01.436 align:middle line:10%
Just kind of make it
dramatic, like wow.

00:21:01.436 --> 00:21:05.525 align:middle line:90%


00:21:05.525 --> 00:21:07.160 align:middle line:10%
I mean, when I see
the women pass by,

00:21:07.160 --> 00:21:10.650 align:middle line:10%
that's just what I like
to look at. [LAUGHS]

00:21:10.650 --> 00:21:13.494 align:middle line:10%
No, I'm just playing.

00:21:13.494 --> 00:21:16.560 align:middle line:84%
I'm going have a horrible
operation this afternoon.

00:21:16.560 --> 00:21:18.675 align:middle line:84%
They're going to put
a tube through my nose

00:21:18.675 --> 00:21:23.140 align:middle line:84%
into my stomach,
extremely unpleasant.

00:21:23.140 --> 00:21:23.970 align:middle line:90%
But who knows?

00:21:23.970 --> 00:21:25.900 align:middle line:84%
Something wonderful
may come out of it.

00:21:25.900 --> 00:21:26.800 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS]

00:21:26.800 --> 00:21:29.250 align:middle line:10%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:21:29.250 --> 00:21:54.800 align:middle line:90%